---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="How JSONCraft handles your data. All processing is client-side; no data is uploaded, logged, or tracked."
  activeToolId=""
  lang="en"
>
  <div class="flex-1 overflow-auto px-6 py-8">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto space-y-6 text-sm" style="color: var(--color-text-primary);">
      <div>
        <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider mb-2" style="color: var(--color-accent-fg);">Privacy</p>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-1">Privacy Policy</h2>
        <p class="text-xs" style="color: var(--color-text-muted);">Last updated: 2026-04-05</p>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-4 leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--color-text-secondary);">
        <section>
          <h3 class="text-base font-semibold mb-2" style="color: var(--color-text-primary);">Summary</h3>
          <p>
            JSONCraft is a collection of developer tools (JSON, YAML, TOML, XML, CSV, regex, base64, hash, etc.) that run entirely in your browser. We do not collect, store, or transmit the data you paste into any tool.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h3 class="text-base font-semibold mb-2" style="color: var(--color-text-primary);">Data we do <em>not</em> collect</h3>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1">
            <li>No analytics. No cookies for analytics or tracking.</li>
            <li>No server-side logging of JSON, YAML, passwords, tokens, or any data you process.</li>
            <li>No account system — you don't provide us any identity.</li>
            <li>No hidden server calls. Every tool runs 100% in your browser.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h3 class="text-base font-semibold mb-2" style="color: var(--color-text-primary);">Third-party services we use</h3>
          <p class="mb-2">JSONCraft is designed to be fully client-side. We use a minimal set of external services only for rendering and ad delivery:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2">
            <li><strong style="color: var(--color-text-primary);">Self-hosted fonts</strong> — Inter and JetBrains Mono fonts are served directly from our servers. No external font services are used.</li>
            <li><strong style="color: var(--color-text-primary);">Google AdSense</strong> (Google, US) — displays ads. <em>Only loaded after you explicitly accept cookies.</em></li>
            <li><strong style="color: var(--color-text-primary);">Cloudflare</strong> (EU) — hosting and CDN. Standard web server logs (IP, path, user-agent) may be retained by Cloudflare per their policy.</li>
            <li><strong style="color: var(--color-text-primary);">Formspree</strong> (EU) — feedback form submissions. Only invoked when you submit the feedback form in the footer.</li>
          </ul>
          <!-- [ADSENSE-VENDOR-CLAUSE] AdSense Help canonical boilerplate, required for AdSense approval -->
  <p style="margin-top: 1em;"><strong>Third-party vendors, including Google,</strong> use cookies to serve ads based on a user's prior visits to this website or other websites. Google's use of advertising cookies enables it and its partners to serve ads to users based on their visit to this site and/or other sites on the Internet. Users may opt out of personalized advertising by visiting <a href="https://www.google.com/settings/ads" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google Ads Settings</a>. Alternatively, users can opt out of a third-party vendor's use of cookies for personalized advertising by visiting <a href="https://www.aboutads.info/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">www.aboutads.info</a>.</p>
  <!-- [NAMED-PROCESSORS-V1] LSSI Art 22.2 + GDPR Art 13 named-processor disclosures -->
  <h2 style="margin-top: 2em;">Named processors and international transfers</h2>
  <p>The third parties listed below process limited data on our behalf. All US-based processors are certified under the <a href="https://www.dataprivacyframework.gov/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">EU-US Data Privacy Framework</a> (DPF), the lawful transfer mechanism since July 2023.</p>
  <table style="width:100%; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.92em; margin-top: 1em;">
    <thead>
      <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid #888;">
        <th style="text-align:left; padding: 6px 8px;">Processor</th>
        <th style="text-align:left; padding: 6px 8px;">Purpose</th>
        <th style="text-align:left; padding: 6px 8px;">Legal basis</th>
        <th style="text-align:left; padding: 6px 8px;">Retention</th>
        <th style="text-align:left; padding: 6px 8px;">Transfer</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td style="padding:6px 8px;"><strong>Google LLC</strong> (Google AdSense, USA)</td><td style="padding:6px 8px;">Display advertising</td><td style="padding:6px 8px;">Consent (GDPR Art. 6(1)(a))</td><td style="padding:6px 8px;">Up to 13 months (Google default)</td><td style="padding:6px 8px;">DPF</td></tr>
      <tr><td style="padding:6px 8px;"><strong>Google LLC</strong> (Funding Choices CMP, USA)</td><td style="padding:6px 8px;">Cookie consent management (TCF v2.2)</td><td style="padding:6px 8px;">Legal obligation (ePrivacy)</td><td style="padding:6px 8px;">Session</td><td style="padding:6px 8px;">DPF</td></tr>
      <tr><td style="padding:6px 8px;"><strong>Google LLC</strong> (Google Analytics 4, USA)</td><td style="padding:6px 8px;">Aggregate audience measurement (IP-anonymised)</td><td style="padding:6px 8px;">Consent in EU/EEA/UK; legitimate interest elsewhere</td><td style="padding:6px 8px;">14 months</td><td style="padding:6px 8px;">DPF</td></tr>
      <tr><td style="padding:6px 8px;"><strong>Cloudflare, Inc.</strong> (USA, EU edge)</td><td style="padding:6px 8px;">Hosting, CDN, security, anonymous request metrics</td><td style="padding:6px 8px;">Legitimate interest (GDPR Art. 6(1)(f))</td><td style="padding:6px 8px;">Aggregate logs, ≤30 days</td><td style="padding:6px 8px;">DPF + EU DPA</td></tr>
      <tr><td style="padding:6px 8px;"><strong>Formspree.io</strong> (USA)</td><td style="padding:6px 8px;">Footer feedback form submissions (only when you submit)</td><td style="padding:6px 8px;">Consent (GDPR Art. 6(1)(a))</td><td style="padding:6px 8px;">Per Formspree policy</td><td style="padding:6px 8px;">DPF</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
  <p style="margin-top: 1em;"><strong>Right to object (GDPR Art. 21):</strong> you may object to any processing based on legitimate interest at any time by contacting us via the footer form. <strong>Right to withdraw consent (GDPR Art. 7(3)):</strong> you may withdraw consent at any time via the cookie banner (it reappears when you clear localStorage for this site). Withdrawal does not affect lawfulness of processing prior to withdrawal.</p>
</section>

        <section>
          <h3 class="text-base font-semibold mb-2" style="color: var(--color-text-primary);">Advertising (Google AdSense)</h3>
          <p class="mb-2">
            We use Google AdSense to show advertisements. AdSense sets cookies and may use your IP address to serve personalized ads. These cookies are only loaded <em>after</em> you explicitly accept the consent banner. If you decline, no AdSense scripts are loaded.
          </p>
          <p>
            More info: <a href="https://policies.google.com/technologies/ads" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="underline hover:text-[var(--color-accent)]">Google Ads privacy policy</a>.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h3 class="text-base font-semibold mb-2" style="color: var(--color-text-primary);">Local storage</h3>
          <p>We store two small values in your browser's localStorage:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1">
            <li><code>jsoncraft-theme</code> — your preferred color theme (light or dark).</li>
            <li><code>cookie-consent</code> — whether you accepted or declined the cookie banner.</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-2">These values never leave your browser.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h3 class="text-base font-semibold mb-2" style="color: var(--color-text-primary);">Your rights (GDPR)</h3>
          <p>
            Because we store no personal data, there is nothing to access, delete, or export. You can withdraw consent for AdSense cookies at any time by clearing your browser's localStorage for this site — the consent banner will reappear on your next visit.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h3 class="text-base font-semibold mb-2" style="color: var(--color-text-primary);">Contact</h3>
          <p>Questions? Use the feedback form in the footer.</p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
